com.facebook.buck.event.listener

Class AbstractConsoleEventBusListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.event.listener.AbstractConsoleEventBusListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BuckEventListener, Closeable, AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SilentConsoleEventBusListener, SimpleConsoleEventBusListener, SuperConsoleEventBusListener

    public abstract class AbstractConsoleEventBusListener
extends Object
implements BuckEventListener
    Base class for BuckEventListeners responsible for outputting information about the running build to stderr.

      • getEventsBetween

        protected static Collection<EventInterval> getEventsBetween(long start,
                                                            long end,
                                                            Iterable<EventInterval> eventIntervals)
        Filter a list of events and return the subset that fall between the given start and end timestamps. Preserves ordering if the given iterable was ordered. Will replace event pairs that straddle the boundary with ProxyBuckEvent instances, so that the resulting collection is strictly contained within the boundaries.
        Parameters:
        start - the start timestamp (inclusive)
        end - the end timestamp (also inclusive)
        eventIntervals - the events to filter.
        Returns:
        a list of all events from the given iterable that fall between the given start and end times. If an event straddles the given start or end, it will be replaced with a proxy event pair that cuts off at exactly the start or end.

      • logEventInterval

        protected long logEventInterval(String prefix,
                                Optional<String> suffix,
                                long currentMillis,
                                long offsetMs,
                                @Nullable
                                BuckEvent startEvent,
                                @Nullable
                                BuckEvent finishedEvent,
                                Optional<Double> progress,
                                Optional<Long> minimum,
                                com.google.common.collect.ImmutableList.Builder<String> lines)
        Adds a line about a pair of start and finished events to lines.
        Parameters:
        prefix - Prefix to print for this event pair.
        suffix - Suffix to print for this event pair.
        currentMillis - The current time in milliseconds.
        offsetMs - Offset to remove from calculated time. Set this to a non-zero value if the event pair would contain another event. For example, build time includes parse time, but to make the events easier to reason about it makes sense to pull parse time out of build time.
        startEvent - The started event.
        finishedEvent - The finished event.
        lines - The builder to append lines to.
        Returns:
        The amount of time between start and finished if finished is present, otherwise UNFINISHED_EVENT_PAIR.

      • logEventInterval

        @Deprecated
protected long logEventInterval(String prefix,
                                            Optional<String> suffix,
                                            long currentMillis,
                                            long offsetMs,
                                            Collection<EventInterval> eventIntervals,
                                            Optional<Double> progress,
                                            Optional<Long> minimum,
                                            com.google.common.collect.ImmutableList.Builder<String> lines)
        Deprecated. 
        Adds a line about a set of start and finished events to lines.
        Parameters:
        prefix - Prefix to print for this event pair.
        suffix - Suffix to print for this event pair.
        currentMillis - The current time in milliseconds.
        offsetMs - Offset to remove from calculated time. Set this to a non-zero value if the event pair would contain another event. For example, build time includes parse time, but to make the events easier to reason about it makes sense to pull parse time out of build time.
        eventIntervals - the collection of start/end events to sum up when calculating elapsed time.
        lines - The builder to append lines to.
        Returns:
        The summed time between start and finished events if each start event has a matching finished event, otherwise UNFINISHED_EVENT_PAIR.

      • getWorkingTimeFromLastStartUntilNow

        @Deprecated
protected static long getWorkingTimeFromLastStartUntilNow(Collection<EventInterval> eventIntervals,
                                                                      long currentMillis)
        Deprecated. 
        Takes a collection of start and finished events. If there are any events that have a start, but no finished time, the collection is considered ongoing.
        Parameters:
        eventIntervals - the collection of event starts/stops.
        currentMillis - the current time.
        Returns:
        -1 if all events are completed, otherwise the time elapsed between the latest event and currentMillis.

        Get the summed elapsed time from all matched event pairs. Does not consider unmatched event pairs. Pairs are determined by their EventKey.
        Parameters:
        eventIntervals - a set of paired events (incomplete events are okay).
        Returns:
        the sum of all times between matched event pairs.
